&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed Term - 6 Months&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time Specialist Practitioner post to join the North Bristol Crisis team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role involves carrying out frontline assessments, creating care plans, telephone triage, completing risk assessments, and working within a experienced and skilled team, for people experiencing a mental health crisis and supporting them within their own home. A significant part of our work incorporates vital carer and family support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team offers 1:1 supervision, and supports professional development goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a friendly and dynamic 24 hour team that covers the whole of North Bristol and are based in the grounds of Southmead Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of working within community mental health services would be an advantage, alongside a willingness to be part of providing 24 hour, 365 days a year cover, including waking nights.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be need to be able to drive and have a full UK licence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rebecca Eatwell&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team Manager - Rebecca Eatwell or Senior Practitioner - Stephen Murphy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0117 4147170&lt;/p&gt;
